"Castro-Borges P., Mendoza-Rangel J.M.","Influence of climate change on concrete durability in Yucatan peninsula",2010,"Corrosion Engineering Science and Technology","45","1",,"61","69",,,10.1179/147842209X12489567719662,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77949284130&partnerID=40&md5=b3f014201f713ff5a8e0f53ccee65031","Centro de Investigación y de Estudios Avanzados Del IPN, Unidad Mérida, A.P. 73 Cordemex, CP 97310, Mérida, Yucatán, Mexico","Castro-Borges, P., Centro de Investigación y de Estudios Avanzados Del IPN, Unidad Mérida, A.P. 73 Cordemex, CP 97310, Mérida, Yucatán, Mexico; Mendoza-Rangel, J.M., Centro de Investigación y de Estudios Avanzados Del IPN, Unidad Mérida, A.P. 73 Cordemex, CP 97310, Mérida, Yucatán, Mexico","The environmental effects of global climate change (GCC) are becoming more evident. Nonetheless, efforts to document its effects on the durability of infrastructure are still limited. The present study used long term data (1961-2008) on temperature, relative humidity, precipitation and evaporation recorded in a tropical microclimate of the port of Progreso (Yucatan, Mexico) in order to detect climatic patterns associated to GCC. In addition, the authors analysed chloride profiles in concretes of different quality but of the same age (15 years) and exposed to the same microclimate. Results suggest the presence of environmental changes associated to GCC during the last 40 years, especially in terms of average and maximum temperature, which showed increases of 1 and 0·22°C per decade respectively. Results also showed that seasonal and multiannual climatic cycles had an influence on the behaviour of the chloride profile of the studied concretes and thus on their durability. © 2010 Institute of Materials, Minerals and Mining.","Chlorides; Concrete; Durability; Global climatic change; Infrastructure; Temperature","Chloride profiles; Climatic changes; Climatic cycles; Concrete durability; Environmental change; Environmental effects; Global climate changes; Long term; Maximum temperature; Me-xico; Relative humidities; Yucatan; Yucatan peninsula; Atmospheric humidity; Chlorine compounds; Concretes; Durability; Climate change",,,,,,"IPCC 2007: 'Synthesis Report 2007 An Assessment of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change', 1-52, p. 2007; Dye, C., Reiter, P., (2000) Science, 289, pp. 1697-1698; Epstein, P.R., (1999) Science, 285, pp. 347-348; Holden, C., (2009) Science, 323, p. 193; Vorosmarty, C.J., Fekete, B.M., Meybeck, M., Lammers, R., (2000) Science, 289, pp. 284-288; Kerr, R., (2007) Science, 316, pp. 188-190; Meehl, G., Washington, W.M., Collins, W.D., Arblaster, J.M., Hu, A., Buja, L.E., Strand, W.G., Teng, H., (2005) Science, 307, p. 1769; Etkins, R., Epstein, E., (1982) Science, 215, p. 287; Karl, T.R., Trenberth, K.E., (2003) Science, 302, pp. 1719-1723; (2007) CSIRO: 'Infrastructure and Climate Change Risk Assessment for Victoria', , Victoria, Australia, CSIRO; Kintisch, E., (2008) Science, 319, pp. 1744-1745; Denault, C., Millar, R.G., Lence, B.J., (2002) Proc. Annual Conf., pp. 1-10. , Canadian Society for Civil Engineering, Montreal, Quebec, Canada, June, Canadian Society for Civil Engineering; Gaynor, R., (1987) ACI-SP-102-11, , (ed. F. W. Gibson) Detroit, American Concrete Institute; Castro, P., Sagües, A.A., Moreno, E.I., Genescá, J., (1996) Corrosion, (52), pp. 609-617; Wilkins, N.J.M., Lawrence, P.F., (1983) Corrosion of Reinforcement in Concrete Construction, 119. , (ed. A. P. Crane), London, Ellis Horwood; González, J.A., (1989) Control of the Corrosion Study and Measurements by Electrochemical Tecnics, 337. , Madrid, CENIM-CSIC; Feliú, S., Andrade, C., (1992) Handbook of Inspection of Building Works Damaged by Reinforced Corrosion', 122. , Madrid, España, CSIC; Kessler, R.J., Arrebola, V.E., Lingerfelt, R.S., Brown, R.P., Determination of low levels of chloride in concrete and raw materials (1978) Research Report 203 FL. DOT; Arya, C., Buenfeld, N.R., Newman, J.B., (1